               <arr name="dc.description">
                  <str>This interview schedule was used to conduct research for a PhD study on the significance of intercultural understanding in the Key Stage 3 MFL curriculum in England. The study explored three perspectives, one of which was the pupil perspective. The pupil perspective was investigated using mixed methods (questionnaire (n=765) and group interviews (n=6)). The research with pupils was concerned with the following questions: - How interesting or enjoyable do pupils perceive their current experience of (inter)cultural aspects of the MFL curriculum? Would a greater emphasis be welcomed? - Do pupils think it is important that school education encourages them to develop openness to other cultures? - Do pupils consider the acquisition of IU beneficial to their (future) lives outside school? - How might pupils' perceptions vary according to gender / socio-economic group / type of school attended? The qualitative data from the group interviews were compared with the quantitative data from the questionnaire (which is also available from the IRIS repository).</str>
               </arr>
